-- France's CDC says would own 3 pct of new SFR entity
-- By Matthieu Protard
-- Thu Mar 20, 2014 01:30PM EDT
-- None



PARIS, March 20 (Reuters) - French state-backed bank CDC fund said on Thursday it would participate in the new offer made by French conglomerate Bouygues <BOUY.PA> for Vivendi's <VIV.PA> SFR unit and would end up owning around 3 percent of the new combined entity.

A spokesperson for CDC also told Reuters the bank would contribute up to 300 million euros to the new offer.